{"parse":{"title":"Coffin portrait","pageid":13037434,"revid":815037681,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Coffin_portrait_of_Jan_Gniewosz.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Coffin_portrait_of_Jan_Gniewosz.jpg/300px-Coffin_portrait_of_Jan_Gniewosz.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"258\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Coffin_portrait_of_Jan_Gniewosz.jpg/450px-Coffin_portrait_of_Jan_Gniewosz.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/Coffin_portrait_of_Jan_Gniewosz.jpg/600px-Coffin_portrait_of_Jan_Gniewosz.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"661\" data-file-height=\"568\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Coffin_portrait_of_Jan_Gniewosz.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Coffin portrait of Jan Gniewosz, c. 1700, oil on tin plate. <br />Signature: <i><b>I</b>.[an] <b>G</b>.[niewosz] <b>N</b>.[a] <b>O</b>.[oleksowie] <b>K</b>.[asztelan] <b>C</b>.[zchowski]</i><br /> English: <span lang=\"en\">Jan Gniewosz [lord] of <a href=\"/wiki/Oleks%C3%B3w\" title=\"Oleks\u00f3w\">Oleks\u00f3w</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Castellan\" title=\"Castellan\">castellan</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Czch%C3%B3w\" title=\"Czch\u00f3w\">Czch\u00f3w</a></span><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Portrety_trumienne_Muzeum_Narodowe_w_Warszawie.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Portrety_trumienne_Muzeum_Narodowe_w_Warszawie.JPG/200px-Portrety_trumienne_Muzeum_Narodowe_w_Warszawie.JPG\" width=\"200\" height=\"134\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Portrety_trumienne_Muzeum_Narodowe_w_Warszawie.JPG/300px-Portrety_trumienne_Muzeum_Narodowe_w_Warszawie.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/af/Portrety_trumienne_Muzeum_Narodowe_w_Warszawie.JPG/400px-Portrety_trumienne_Muzeum_Narodowe_w_Warszawie.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"4727\" data-file-height=\"3160\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Portrety_trumienne_Muzeum_Narodowe_w_Warszawie.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Coffin portraits in the <a href=\"/wiki/National_Museum_in_Warsaw\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"National Museum in Warsaw\">National Museum in Warsaw</a></div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>coffin portrait</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Polish_language\" title=\"Polish language\">Polish</a>: <i><span lang=\"pl\">Portret trumienny</span></i>) was a realistic <a href=\"/wiki/Portrait\" title=\"Portrait\">portrait</a> of the deceased person put on <a href=\"/wiki/Coffin\" title=\"Coffin\">coffins</a> for the funeral and one of the elements of the <a href=\"/wiki/Castrum_doloris\" title=\"Castrum doloris\">castrum doloris</a>, but removed before the burial. It became a tradition to decorate coffins of deceased nobles (<i><a href=\"/wiki/Szlachta\" title=\"Szlachta\">szlachta</a></i>) with such <a href=\"/wiki/Funerary_art\" title=\"Funerary art\">funerary art</a> in the times of the <a href=\"/wiki/Polish-Lithuanian_Commonwealth\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth\">Polish-Lithuanian Commonwealth</a>, particularly in the 17th and 18th centuries, the time of the <a href=\"/wiki/Baroque_in_Poland\" title=\"Baroque in Poland\">baroque in Poland</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Sarmatism\" title=\"Sarmatism\">Sarmatism</a>. The tradition was limited to Commonwealth countries,<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (April 2008)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> although the term may also describe the <a href=\"/wiki/Fayum_mummy_portraits\" title=\"Fayum mummy portraits\">Ancient Egyptian mummy portraits</a>.<sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (April 2008)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Design\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Design</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Cultural_importance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Cultural importance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Sources\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sources</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Design\">Design</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coffin_portrait&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Design\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>They were commonly painted on <a href=\"/wiki/Sheet_metal\" title=\"Sheet metal\">sheet metal</a> (copper, tin or lead plates) and fixed on the narrow ends of the coffins at the side where the head of the deceased lay. On the opposite of the coffin there was usually an <a href=\"/wiki/Epitaph\" title=\"Epitaph\">epitaph</a>, and the sides held a <a href=\"/wiki/Coat_of_arms\" title=\"Coat of arms\">coat of arms</a>. The shape of the upper edges of the portraits was based on the shape of the coffin, and the lower edges were often used to turn the whole into a <a href=\"/wiki/Hexagon\" title=\"Hexagon\">hexagon</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Octagon\" title=\"Octagon\">octagon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> After the <a href=\"/wiki/Funeral\" title=\"Funeral\">funeral</a>, the coffin portrait would often be hung on the walls of the church that the deceased had contributed to. In time, they increased in size \u2013 from 40 x 45&#160;cm in the 17th century, to 70 x 72&#160;cm in the 18th century.\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:202px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Portrety_trumienne.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/39/Portrety_trumienne.jpg/200px-Portrety_trumienne.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/39/Portrety_trumienne.jpg 1.5x\" data-file-width=\"300\" data-file-height=\"300\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Portrety_trumienne.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Coffin portraits on display at <a href=\"/wiki/Pozna%C5%84_Cathedral\" title=\"Pozna\u0144 Cathedral\">Pozna\u0144 Cathedral</a>, painters unknown.</div></div></div>\n<p>The portraits were highly realistic, with the intent to create an impression that the deceased is taking part in their own funeral; that impression was reinforced often by the subject of the portrait gazing directly at the viewers. Some of them were painted during the life of the deceased.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cultural_importance\">Cultural importance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coffin_portrait&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Cultural importance\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Historian <a href=\"/wiki/Bernard_O%27Connor_(historian)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bernard O&#39;Connor (historian)\">Bernard O'Connor</a> in his memoirs of 1696 wrote: \"There is so much pomp and ceremony in Polish funerals that you would sooner take them to be a triumphant event than the burial of the dead\". Indeed, for Polish nobles (<a href=\"/wiki/Szlachta\" title=\"Szlachta\">szlachta</a>), a proper funeral was extremely important. Those who could afford it spent lavishly on the funeral ceremonies, turning them into major events. But even the poor would try to have at least a basic coffin portrait, albeit those, painted by amateur painters, usually have little or no artistic merit.\n</p><p>Until the 20th century, the coffin portraits were ignored by scholars; those painted on silver or tin were stolen from churches and monasteries and then melted down, others were destroyed by treasure hunters and thieves, or simply fell to the ravages of time. Today the surviving coffin portraits provide a wealth of knowledge about culture (clothing, hairstyles and jewellery) of the Commonwealth nobility. Many coffin portraits are still displayed in various churches across Poland; hundreds are held in various museums.\n</p><p>The oldest coffin portrait in Poland is that of the king <a href=\"/wiki/Stephen_B%C3%A1thory_of_Poland\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Stephen B\u00e1thory of Poland\">Stefan Batory</a> from the late 16th century. The most recent one is that of priest Marcin Porczy\u0144ski from 1809.\n</p>\n<ul class=\"gallery mw-gallery-traditional\" style=\"max-width: 729px;_width: 729px;\">\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 235px\"><div style=\"width: 235px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 230px;\"><div style=\"margin:15px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Coffin_portrait_of_Barbara_Lubomirska.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Coffin_portrait_of_Barbara_Lubomirska.jpg/198px-Coffin_portrait_of_Barbara_Lubomirska.jpg\" width=\"198\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Coffin_portrait_of_Barbara_Lubomirska.jpg/297px-Coffin_portrait_of_Barbara_Lubomirska.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e0/Coffin_portrait_of_Barbara_Lubomirska.jpg/396px-Coffin_portrait_of_Barbara_Lubomirska.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"995\" data-file-height=\"1005\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Coffin portrait of Barbara Lubomirska, 1676.\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 235px\"><div style=\"width: 235px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 230px;\"><div style=\"margin:18.5px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Coffin_portrait_of_Stanis%C5%82aw_Woysza.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Coffin_portrait_of_Stanis%C5%82aw_Woysza.jpg/200px-Coffin_portrait_of_Stanis%C5%82aw_Woysza.jpg\" width=\"200\" height=\"193\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Coffin_portrait_of_Stanis%C5%82aw_Woysza.jpg/300px-Coffin_portrait_of_Stanis%C5%82aw_Woysza.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Coffin_portrait_of_Stanis%C5%82aw_Woysza.jpg/400px-Coffin_portrait_of_Stanis%C5%82aw_Woysza.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"687\" data-file-height=\"663\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Coffin portrait of Stanis\u0142aw Woysz, 1677.\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n\t\t<li class=\"gallerybox\" style=\"width: 235px\"><div style=\"width: 235px\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"thumb\" style=\"width: 230px;\"><div style=\"margin:32px auto;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Portret_trumienny_z_Olkusza.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Portret_trumienny_z_Olkusza.JPG/200px-Portret_trumienny_z_Olkusza.JPG\" width=\"200\" height=\"166\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Portret_trumienny_z_Olkusza.JPG/300px-Portret_trumienny_z_Olkusza.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Portret_trumienny_z_Olkusza.JPG/400px-Portret_trumienny_z_Olkusza.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"532\" data-file-height=\"441\" /></a></div></div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"gallerytext\">\n<p>Coffin portrait of Baltazar Horlemes, 1682.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coffin_portrait&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Fayum_mummy_portraits\" title=\"Fayum mummy portraits\">Fayum mummy portraits</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Funeral_Crown\" title=\"Funeral Crown\">Funeral Crown</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/O%C5%9Bwi%C4%99cim_Chapel\" title=\"O\u015bwi\u0119cim Chapel\">O\u015bwi\u0119cim Chapel</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coffin_portrait&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20020610034517/http://www.gniewoszow.pl/historia.htm\">\"Oleks\u00f3w\"</a>. <i>www.gniewoszow.pl</i> (in Polish). Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.gniewoszow.pl/historia.htm\">the original</a> on 2002-06-10<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-05-19</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.gniewoszow.pl&amp;rft.atitle=Oleks%C3%B3w&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gniewoszow.pl%2Fhistoria.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACoffin+portrait\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Mariusz Karpowicz (1991). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=A3lZAAAAIAAJ&amp;pgis=1\"><i>Baroque in Poland</i></a>. Arkady. p.&#160;68. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/83-213-3412-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/83-213-3412-1\">83-213-3412-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Baroque+in+Poland&amp;rft.pages=68&amp;rft.pub=Arkady&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.isbn=83-213-3412-1&amp;rft.au=Mariusz+Karpowicz&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DA3lZAAAAIAAJ%26pgis%3D1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACoffin+portrait\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Piotr Krasny. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.autoportret.pl/_files/artykuly/8a7ade2a8455dd13fc096b83edf587cf.pdf\">\"Wizerunki zmar\u0142ych w sztuce\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <i>www.autoportret.pl</i> (in Polish). p.&#160;2<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-05-19</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.autoportret.pl&amp;rft.atitle=Wizerunki+zmar%C5%82ych+w+sztuce&amp;rft.pages=2&amp;rft.au=Piotr+Krasny&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.autoportret.pl%2F_files%2Fartykuly%2F8a7ade2a8455dd13fc096b83edf587cf.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACoffin+portrait\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\"><span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot\" title=\"Wikipedia:Link rot\"><span title=\"&#160;Dead link since October 2010\">dead link</span></a></i>&#93;</span></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coffin_portrait&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Jan K. Ostrowski, <i>Land of the Winged Horsemen: Art in Poland, 1572-1764</i>, Yale University Press, 1999, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-300-07918-4\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-300-07918-4\">0-300-07918-4</a>, p.&#160;279 <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=ucOZCQMVMNIC&amp;pg=PA279&amp;dq=%22Coffin+portrait%22&amp;ei=5Y3YRokvm4jsAvuHpO8F&amp;sig=sw2ezTGzTdGUL7XRupHoSdr01OQ#PPA279,M1\">Google Print</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.warsawvoice.pl/archiwum.phtml/7253/\">The Theater of Transition: COFFIN PORTRAITS</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Warsaw_Voice\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Warsaw Voice\">Warsaw Voice</a>, 23 February 1997</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_reading\">Further reading</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Coffin_portrait&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Further reading\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Andrew Ciechanowiecki, <i>Polish Art Treasures at the Royal Academy</i>, The Burlington Magazine, Vol. 112, No. 803, Italian Sixteenth-Century Art outside Venice (Feb., 1970), pp.&#160;120\u2013124, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.jstor.org/stable/876239\">JSTOR</a></li>\n<li>Review of <i>Smierc w kulturze dawnej Polski od sredniowiecza do konca XVIII wieku: Przerazliwe echo traby zaosnej do wiecznosci wzywajacej</i> [Death in Polish Culture from the Middle Ages until the End of the Eighteenth Century: The Terrifying Sound of the Mourning Trumpet Summoning the Dead to the Other World] by Przemysaw Mrozowski, Krystyna Moisan-Jabonska, Janusz Nowinski. Author of Review: Katarzyna Murawska-Muthesius. The Burlington Magazine, Vol. 143, No. 1185 (Dec., 2001), pp.&#160;762\u2013763 <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=